 * Helps to print the token in a formatted way.

 *
 * Longest OpCode is 12 characters long so default padding is set to 12 characters. This padding does not include an mandatory space between the OpCode and parameters. Padding only happens to instructions with parameters.
 *
 * @example
 * ```
 * const script = "210c0500000000014101020304"
 * console.log(OpToken.fromScript(script).map(t => t.prettyPrint()));
 * //NOP
 * //PUSHDATA1     0000000001
 * //SYSCALL       01020304
 *
 * console.log(OpToken.fromScript(script).map(t => t.prettyPrint(8))); //underpad
 * //NOP
